Note: This project contains reverse-engineered protocol documentation derived
from observing BLE traffic between the official myClaber app and the device.
No proprietary code or copyrighted assets from Claber S.p.A. are included.

The sole purpose of this work is **interoperability** — specifically, enabling
the device to be controlled via Home Assistant without relying on the vendor's
cloud or app. This is not intended for product development, competition with
Claber S.p.A., or any commercial use. Claber and myAquaSolar are trademarks of
Claber S.p.A. This project is not affiliated with or endorsed by Claber S.p.A.

In the EU, Directive 2009/24/EC permits the observation of a lawfully acquired
program's behaviour (Art. 5(3)) and decompilation of its code (Art. 6) when
these acts are indispensable to achieve interoperability of an independently
created program with other programs or devices, provided the resulting
information is used solely for that purpose. The reverse engineering performed
here was conducted by lawful users of the device and the official app, was
limited to what is necessary for interoperability with Home Assistant, and the
information is not used to develop a substantially similar competing product.
